  "text": "A novel amine oxidase, renalase, which metabolizes catecholamines, was recently discovered [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Through its regulation of catecholamines, renalase lowers blood pressure. It also regulates sodium and phosphate exertion, and displays other cardioprotective effects through currently unknown mechanisms [CITATION_3] ). Plasma renalase is activated by moderate increases in blood pressure and brief surges of plasma catecholamines, which also lead to increased renalase production and secretion [CITATION_4] .",
